        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 7:41PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 741 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Catholic Point, or 15 miles south of Clinton, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fairfield Bay...                  Quitman...
Guy...                            Damascus...
Twin Groves...                    Shirley...
Fairfield Bay Marina...           Catholic Point...
Fairbanks...                      Mallet Town...
Whipple...                        Sugar Loaf Recreation Area...
Choctaw...                        Springfield...
Woolly Hollow State Park...       Bee Branch...
Austin in Conway County...        Formosa...
Center Ridge...                   Choctow Recreation Area...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
